# LiqXanMod hybrid glue patch series
#
# These patches are applied AFTER the Zen/Liquorix patches and BEFORE the
# XanMod-specific scheduler patches. Their purpose is to:
#
#   1. Expose Zen scheduler tunables (zen_latency_ns, zen_burst_penalty) via
#      sysfs so the runtime autodetect module can adjust them without a reboot.
#
#   2. Add a Kconfig symbol (CONFIG_LIQXANMOD_HYBRID) that gates the
#      autodetect module and the dual-scheduler sysfs bridge.
#
#   3. Rename any symbol that both XanMod and Zen define identically to avoid
#      duplicate-symbol link errors (e.g. sched_nr_latency).
#
# Patches are listed one per line, relative to this directory.
# Lines starting with # are comments. Blank lines are ignored.
#
# ── Conflict map ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The table below documents every known symbol conflict between XanMod 6.x
# and Zen 6.x patches and how each is resolved.
#
# Symbol / file                  XanMod change      Zen change        Resolution
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# kernel/sched/fair.c            wakeup_gran tweak  latency_ns tweak  Zen wins;
#                                                                      XanMod
#                                                                      value
#                                                                      exposed
#                                                                      via sysfs
# kernel/sched/core.c            nr_latency bump    nr_latency bump   Zen wins
# include/linux/sched/sysctl.h   sched_nr_latency   sched_nr_latency  deduplicated
#                                                                      by glue
# mm/page_alloc.c                watermark tweak    watermark tweak   Zen wins
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# To add a new glue patch:
#   1. Create the .patch file in this directory.
#   2. Add its filename on a new line below.
#   3. Document the conflict it resolves in the table above.

0001-liqxanmod-kconfig-symbol.patch
0002-liqxanmod-sysfs-bridge.patch
0003-liqxanmod-dedup-sched-nr-latency.patch
